content.text:
Done. Esc now closes the right dock whether it's showing the Status or Artifacts tab.

The change is in `src/App.tsx`'s global hotkey handler (`src/App.tsx:830`):

```js
// Esc closes the right dock (Status or Artifacts tab) when it's open.
// The settings modal and find bar handle their own Esc, so defer to them.
if (e.key === "Escape" && dockOpen && view === "chat" && !showSettings) {
  e.preventDefault();
  setDockOpen(false);
  return;
}
```

A few notes on the guards:
- `dockOpen && view === "chat"` matches the existing `showDock` condition — the dock only renders alongside the chat, so Esc only fires when it's actually visible.
- `!showSettings` defers to the settings modal, which has its own Esc-to-close handler.
- The find bar (in `ChatView`) also closes on Esc independently; if both the find bar and dock happen to be open, one Esc closes both. If you'd rather Esc close them one at a time, let me know and I can thread the find state up.

Typecheck passes.

